oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cutting lumber in Pine Top
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph showing lumber being cut in Pine Top for the construction of Western State Hospital. Two unidentified men can be seen (on right) next to a wagon being pulled by oxen and bulls.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Men; Carts & wagons; Cattle; Lumber industry
